MS PATHS Data Curation Policy
Why do standards matter?
â€¢ To ensure uniform and consistent meaning for clinical data elements
â€¢ To promote system-agnostic and site-agnostic curation method that relies on common terminology
and semantics
â€¢ To ensure that harmonization is not reliant on any one form of data transmission or data storage
Our position: To harmonize clinical data by using industry-accepted clinical terminology
standard libraries/data sets
â€¢ SNOMED CTÂ®: smoking status, social history, problems
â€¢ LOINCÂ®: lab orders, lab results, vital signs
â€¢ RxNorm and NDC: medications
â€¢ HCPCS: DMEs
